description: Lexicographically earliest infinite sequence such that a(i) = a(j) => A336158(i) = A336158(j), A336466(i) = A336466(j) and A336467(i) = A336467(j) for all i, j >= 1, where A336466 is fully multiplicative with a(p) = oddpart(p-1) for any prime p and A336467 is fully multiplicative with a(2) = 1 and a(p) = oddpart(p+1) for odd primes, and A336158(n) gives the prime signature of the odd part of n.
